                  , in and upon the back part of his head, giving to him, the said James, one mortal fracture of the scull of the length of three inches, and of the breadth of two inches, of which he languished until the third day of the same month, and then died; and that the said 
                     
                        <persName id="t17780603-69-defend542" type="defendantName">
                           Elizabeth
